d><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Girl(shiny) with Sniper Rifle</span><hr size=1> Ok, time for me to comment on the firearm cause that is what I know best.<br>
It looks nice, except the whole thing looks kinda bent. The bipod is too big. so is the handle. VMI may correct me on this, but from what I have heard bullpup weapons are very hard to snipe with. Usually they have a slightly longer barrel than a standard assault rifle but the way you hold them is for quick movements not for pinpoint accuracy. Scope seems to be sitting a little high too. This isn't really a sniper rifle but a modded assault rifle for longer range. Not very many snipers would be caught taking a 5.56 NATO out to snipe with.<br>
I may sound harsh, I don't mean it to be. The line control seems very good to me, and just a bit more knowledge of the design and how it should work will assist you in future drawings and they will be more realistic and/or better. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uburncycle360.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Burncycle360</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/13/01 9:25:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4108.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Girl(shiny) with Sniper Rifle</span><hr size=1> Sure, you can snipe with it. In fact, Bullpups (though takes some getting used to) are in some ways better at sniping because for the same length weapon, you can have a longer barrel which means more muzzle velocity and hopefully more accuracy. Or you can keep the same length barrel and have a shorter, less bulky, assult weapon. You just have to get used to the different center of balance.<br>
<br>
This is more of a intermediate ranged sniper weapon. Not an M40 or .50 caliber designed for long ranges.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uvmirat.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VMI rat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/14/01 11:43:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4108.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://falloutboy33.multimania.com//k1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Girl(shiny) with Sniper Rifle</span><hr size=1> hmm.. actually i dont really consider it a sniper rifle at all. it is just one of those trend military firearm design is going through right now: army of one mentality. designing an ultimate firearm that can put the role of a sniper and support gunner into a grunt. unfortunately like most things jack of all trade is king of none. most &quot;professional&quot; sniper would still prefer a delicated sniper rifle like m40 or l96. like hellion said, 5.56mm is really not design for sniping. while ill admit to the fact that bullpup hav its advantage, sniping is really not it's role. it does hav better accuracy but field stripping/clean which a sniper must do on a frequant basis is a problem for bullpup. and also the chamber and port are next to the sniper's head might be a problem.   <p>"Gotta get in tune with Sailor Moon 'Cause that cartoon has got the boom anime babes That make me think the wrong thing." 
